### **🛡️ Middleware Layer**

#### `middleware/errorHandler.js`
**Purpose**: Catches ALL errors and returns consistent responses

```javascript
// errorHandler(err, req, res, next)
// - Logs error details
// - Handles Prisma errors (P2025, P2002, etc.)
// - Returns formatted error response
// - Prevents server crashes

// asyncHandler(fn)
// - Wraps async functions
// - Catches promises and passes to errorHandler
// - Used in all controllers
```

**When to use:**
```javascript
const getInvoices = asyncHandler(async (req, res) => {
    // Errors automatically caught and handled
});
```

#### `middleware/validation.js`
**Purpose**: Validates request data BEFORE processing

```javascript
// validateRequestBody({ requiredFields, customValidator })
// - Checks required fields exist
// - Runs custom validation logic
// - Returns 400 if invalid

// sanitizeInput(req, res, next)
// - Trims whitespace
// - Cleans string inputs
// - Prevents XSS attacks
```

**When to use:**
```javascript
router.post("/invoice", 
    sanitizeInput,
    validateRequestBody({ requiredFields: ["InvNumber", "SellerName"] }),
    controller.createInvoice
);
```

#### `middleware/auth.js`
**Purpose**: Protects routes with JWT authentication

**When to use:**
```javascript
router.get("/dashboard", auth, controller.getDashboard); // Protected
```

