## 🔄 **REQUEST FLOW ARCHITECTURE**

```
CLIENT REQUEST
    ↓
[ROUTE] routes/*.js
    - Maps URL to controller
    - router.get("/path", controller.method)
    ↓
[MIDDLEWARE]
    - sanitizeInput → cleans data
    - validateRequestBody → validates data
    - auth → checks JWT token
    ↓
[CONTROLLER] controllers/*.js
    - Receives request
    - Calls service
    - Returns response
    ↓
[SERVICE] services/*.js
    - Business logic
    - Data transformation
    - Calls repository
    ↓
[REPOSITORY] repositories/*.js
    - Database queries
    - Prisma ORM / Raw SQL
    ↓
[DATABASE] SQL Server
    - Stores/retrieves data
    ↓
ERROR?
    ↓ YES
[ERROR HANDLER] middleware/errorHandler.js
    - Catches error
    - Logs details
    - Formats response
    ↓
RESPONSE
    - JSON with status code
    - Back to client
```

